<br>
The two are intertwined.  Bush needs some Arab support to depose Saddam Hussein, but this support is conditional on creating some sort of Palestinian state.  Apparently Bush advisors are deeply divided on whether it's even worth going after Saddam, and possibly whether this is a devil's bargain.  <br>
<br>
So a few things are possible:<br>
1) Bush goes after Saddam without any resolution with Israel and Palestine, and has to go it without Arab support.<br>
2) Bush tries to work out some piecemeal accord for the Palestinians but gets nowhere, and the attack on Saddam never occurs.<br>
3) Bush says &quot;screw it&quot; on Saddam for now and supports Israel wholeheartedly.<br>
4) Some miracle occurs and a peace can be established in Israel allowing Bush to go after Saddam.  <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umeddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meddik</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://aodoctors.homestead.com/files/cross.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 1:24:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8901.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.myezboard.com:81/projects/ezboard/ezboard_userimages/aodoctors/images/weeee.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's been a while... so here's another thread on Israel!</span><hr size=1> Why exactly is Arab support so important for an assault on Iraq?<br>
<br>
I know, I know, Its good to have allies, and a coalition and staging bases might make it easier, ro lead to a lower number of casualties.<br>
<br>
But really, there is no reason why we couldn't do it unilaterally (Ooooh. Scary word!) without the support of any of the Arab countries.<br>
<br>
Turkey is a close ally of ours, and I could easily see them allowing us to base out of there, in return for sizeable diplomatic consessions. (They are Muslim, but mostly non-Arab, and are much more likely to side with us than with Iraq. They think Sadaam is a lunatic too.)<br>
<br>
Iran has had frequent pro-american demonstrations since september 11th, largely calling for the overthrow of the government. <br>
<br>
The Saudis? They need our money much mroe than we need their Oil. We can go elsewhere quite easily now, thanks to Russia's increased exports of Oil. They depend on us a lot mroe than we do on them. (Incidentally, I'd like to see a huge amount of our support there removed as well, but thats a secondary concern after Bagdhad.)<br>
<br>
I really don't think that any sort of peace in Israel is needed before all of this, But any attack on Iraq will likely be bad for Israel. Look at the Gulf war. We liberate Kuwait, and Hussein lobs missiles into Israel. Expect more of the same. But as as much as I like Israel, I don't think we can allow Saddam to hold them hostage and stop us from doing what needs to be done. <p><hr><center><a href=http://trojanhorseshoes.blogspot.com/>Trojan Horsehoes</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ukroemagnon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kroe Magnon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://community.theunderdogs.org/smiley/happy/jestera.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/1/02 1:41:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8901.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://macmorrigan.homestead.com/files/funnyraven.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's been a while... so here's another thread on Israel!</span><hr size=1> frighteningly enough I have to agree with meddik about looking closely at our ties with Soudi Arabia, but aside from that the idea of atacking Iraq with little to no local supprt areas would be a tactical nightmare. without local air strips your basic Sorte's become incredibly long and difficult, ground troops placement gets increasingly difficult, and chances of others rising up WITH Iraq becomes a possibility.<br>
<br>
